    fullDescription: 'Murder at the U investigates crimes that happened on university campuses — and the institutional responses that too often prioritized reputation over justice. From unsolved student murders to campus assault cover-ups to hazing deaths swept under the rug, host Isabelle Park documents how universities have repeatedly chosen to protect their brands over the safety of their students.',
